metadata.name: Contemplative Warp
metadata.description:
50 sec .mp4 loop - 2160 x 2160 - 60fps  
---

Through the vastness of the unknown,  
We search for answers, all alone.  
The mysteries of the universe,  
So far away, yet so diverse.

But what if we could cross the line,  
And journey through the vast black brine?  
With a warp, we could bend the space,  
And reach the stars in a fleeting pace.

The fabric of the cosmos would yield,  
As we'd travel at a faster speed.  
Galaxies would blur and fade away,  
In this journey to the Milky Way.

We'd leave behind the earthly strife,  
And bask in the glow of celestial life.  
With the power of the warp in hand,  
We'd explore the universe, expand.

So let us forge ahead, with glee,  
And warp through space, beyond our sea.  
And discover wonders untold,  
As we journey, brave and bold.
